sequenceDiagram
    participant User
    participant CLI as Claude CLI
    participant Loop as Agentic Loop
    participant API as Claude API
    participant SE as StreamingToolExecutor
    participant T1 as Tool (read-only)
    participant T2 as Tool (write)
    participant CM as Context Manager

    User->>CLI: "refactor this module to async"
    CLI->>Loop: start query
    
    Loop->>CM: preprocess context
    CM->>CM: L1: SNIP old tool results
    CM->>CM: L2: Microcompact (cache edit)
    CM-->>Loop: trimmed messages
    
    Loop->>API: stream request (SSE)
    
    Note over API,SE: Model starts generating response...
    
    API-->>Loop: text chunk "Let me analyze..."
    API-->>Loop: tool_use: {grep, pattern: "async"}
    
    Loop->>SE: execute grep (read-only)
    SE->>T1: grep started ⚡
    
    API-->>Loop: text chunk "I see 5 files..."
    API-->>Loop: tool_use: {read_file, "src/main.ts"}
    
    Loop->>SE: execute read_file (read-only)
    SE->>T1: read started ⚡ (parallel!)
    
    Note over T1: Both tools running<br/>while model still talks
    
    T1-->>SE: grep results
    T1-->>SE: file contents
    
    API-->>Loop: tool_use: {write_file, "src/main.ts"}
    Loop->>SE: execute write (exclusive lock)
    SE->>T2: write started 🔒
    T2-->>SE: write complete
    
    API-->>Loop: [stream end]
    
    SE-->>Loop: all results (ordered)
    Loop->>Loop: append results to messages
    Loop->>API: next turn (with tool results)
    
    API-->>Loop: "Done! I've refactored..."
    API-->>Loop: [end_turn, no tools]
    
    Loop-->>CLI: final response
    CLI-->>User: display result
